<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="513" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,567,882]" pageId="7" pageNumber="513">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,271,567,593]" pageId="7" pageNumber="513">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is characterized by male and female with four pairs of dorsocentral setae; wing with brown to black infuscation at level of crossveins r-m and dm-m (
<figureCitation box="[801,891,603,630]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,906,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-207@7.[150,1437,905,1875]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. Macrostomus pictipennis (Bezzi, 1909) from Cuzco, Peru. ♂ (A–D). A. Wing; B. Tergite 8, dorsal view; C. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; D. Hypandrium, lateral view. ♀ (E–F). E. Mid leg, posterior view; F. Hind leg, posterior view. Scale bars, figure A = 1 mm; B–D = 0.2 mm; E–F = 0.5 mm (figures after Rafael &amp; Cumming (2010)).Abbreviations: dm–m—discal medial crossvein; epand, epandrium; r–m—radial–medial crossvein; t, tergite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921361" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921361/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="513">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[911,979,603,629]" pageId="7" pageNumber="513">Male.</emphasis>
Tergite 8 (
<figureCitation box="[1101,1187,603,630]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,906,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-207@7.[150,1437,905,1875]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. Macrostomus pictipennis (Bezzi, 1909) from Cuzco, Peru. ♂ (A–D). A. Wing; B. Tergite 8, dorsal view; C. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; D. Hypandrium, lateral view. ♀ (E–F). E. Mid leg, posterior view; F. Hind leg, posterior view. Scale bars, figure A = 1 mm; B–D = 0.2 mm; E–F = 0.5 mm (figures after Rafael &amp; Cumming (2010)).Abbreviations: dm–m—discal medial crossvein; epand, epandrium; r–m—radial–medial crossvein; t, tergite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921361" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921361/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="513">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
) elongated with distal protuberances; epandrium (
<figureCitation box="[460,546,639,666]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,906,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-207@7.[150,1437,905,1875]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. Macrostomus pictipennis (Bezzi, 1909) from Cuzco, Peru. ♂ (A–D). A. Wing; B. Tergite 8, dorsal view; C. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; D. Hypandrium, lateral view. ♀ (E–F). E. Mid leg, posterior view; F. Hind leg, posterior view. Scale bars, figure A = 1 mm; B–D = 0.2 mm; E–F = 0.5 mm (figures after Rafael &amp; Cumming (2010)).Abbreviations: dm–m—discal medial crossvein; epand, epandrium; r–m—radial–medial crossvein; t, tergite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921361" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921361/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="513">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
) slightly swollen with strong posterodorsal lobe longer than anterodorsal lobe; hypandrium (
<figureCitation box="[302,391,675,702]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,906,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-207@7.[150,1437,905,1875]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. Macrostomus pictipennis (Bezzi, 1909) from Cuzco, Peru. ♂ (A–D). A. Wing; B. Tergite 8, dorsal view; C. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; D. Hypandrium, lateral view. ♀ (E–F). E. Mid leg, posterior view; F. Hind leg, posterior view. Scale bars, figure A = 1 mm; B–D = 0.2 mm; E–F = 0.5 mm (figures after Rafael &amp; Cumming (2010)).Abbreviations: dm–m—discal medial crossvein; epand, epandrium; r–m—radial–medial crossvein; t, tergite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921361" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921361/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="513">Fig. 5D</figureCitation>
) with slender posterior setae; ejaculatory apodeme trilamellar, dorsal lamella absent; phallus same length as hypandrium.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,567,882]" pageId="7" pageNumber="513">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,291,747,773]" pageId="7" pageNumber="513">Female.</emphasis>
Pinnate setae dorsally and ventrally on mid femur and a few short pinnate setae on basal fourth of mid tibia ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[323,409,783,810]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,906,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-207@7.[150,1437,905,1875]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. Macrostomus pictipennis (Bezzi, 1909) from Cuzco, Peru. ♂ (A–D). A. Wing; B. Tergite 8, dorsal view; C. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; D. Hypandrium, lateral view. ♀ (E–F). E. Mid leg, posterior view; F. Hind leg, posterior view. Scale bars, figure A = 1 mm; B–D = 0.2 mm; E–F = 0.5 mm (figures after Rafael &amp; Cumming (2010)).Abbreviations: dm–m—discal medial crossvein; epand, epandrium; r–m—radial–medial crossvein; t, tergite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921361" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921361/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="513">Fig. 5E</figureCitation>
); hind femur and tibia with pinnate setae dorsally and ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[1134,1220,783,810]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,906,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-207@7.[150,1437,905,1875]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. Macrostomus pictipennis (Bezzi, 1909) from Cuzco, Peru. ♂ (A–D). A. Wing; B. Tergite 8, dorsal view; C. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; D. Hypandrium, lateral view. ♀ (E–F). E. Mid leg, posterior view; F. Hind leg, posterior view. Scale bars, figure A = 1 mm; B–D = 0.2 mm; E–F = 0.5 mm (figures after Rafael &amp; Cumming (2010)).Abbreviations: dm–m—discal medial crossvein; epand, epandrium; r–m—radial–medial crossvein; t, tergite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921361" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921361/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="513">Fig. 5F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
